&lt;p&gt;At Later, we are committed to fostering a culture rooted in an &lt;strong&gt;inclusion-first mindset at every level&lt;/strong&gt; of the company, embracing the importance of hiring and &lt;strong&gt;building teams for culture add rather than culture fit&lt;/strong&gt;. We openly build and maintain unbiased hiring, pay, and promotion practices to create a foundation for an equitable workplace, paving the way for systemic change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to creating a &lt;strong&gt;diverse environment&lt;/strong&gt; and are proud to be an&lt;strong&gt; equal opportunity employer&lt;/strong&gt;. All applications will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, national origin, disability, or age. Please let us know if you require any accommodations or support during the recruitment process.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meet Benevity&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Benevity is the way the world does good, providing companies (and their employees) with technology to take social action on the issues they care about. Through giving, volunteering, grantmaking, employee resource groups and micro-actions, we help most of the Fortune 100 brands build better cultures and use their power for good. We’re also one of the first B Corporations in Canada, meaning we’re as committed to purpose as we are to profits. We have people working all over the world, including Canada, Spain, Switzerland, the United Kingdom, the United States and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High-Level Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Operations team is searching for a motivated, self-starting Disbursement Operations Specialist to join us in Calgary. The ideal candidate possesses exceptional critical thinking skills, flexibility to adapt to evolving needs, and an unwavering attention to detail. This individual will thrive on investigating complex payment inquiries, leveraging available resources to solve disbursement-related challenges, and quickly grasping complex global banking requirements. Outstanding communication and interpersonal abilities are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disbursement Resolution &amp;amp; Optimization:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate and resolve all outstanding disbursement issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify trends in payment rejections and collaborate with the Operations Lead and engineering teams to implement solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously enhance disbursement processes while ensuring adherence to foundation and regulatory compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Collaboration &amp;amp; Communication:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain strong working relationships with key Operations and Support stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with our banking partners to address outstanding payment questions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate critical issues and potential resolution strategies to management across functional areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in stakeholder meetings, offering insights to optimize processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up on client and nonprofit inquiries by coordinating with internal teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analysis &amp;amp; Continuous Improvement:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ad-hoc reporting and analysis, managing special projects and other duties as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a culture of continuous improvement, focusing on positive impact for our clients and nonprofits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education/Experience: &lt;/strong&gt;A Bachelor’s Degree or equivalent education/experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analytical &amp;amp; Problem-Solving Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong critical thinking skills and the ability to &quot;think outside the box.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with the capacity to process information accurately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional attention to detail and a commitment to quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable operating in a high-uncertainty environment, demonstrating the ability to navigate ambiguous processes and proactively figure out solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Proficiency:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in the MS Office Suite, with advanced skills in Excel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Desirable: &lt;/em&gt;Experience using an Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) system, such as Oracle ERP, is desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Asset:&lt;/em&gt; Experience with data visualization or Business Intelligence tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Asset:&lt;/em&gt; A strong technical mindset and experience leveraging AI for process improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Asset:&lt;/em&gt; Previous experience with global disbursements or international payment processing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Organizational &amp;amp; Interpersonal Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational skills, capable of managing multiple deliverables under tight deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independent working skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills, with the ability to convey findings effectively to non-technical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discover your purpose at work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re not employees, we’re Benevity-ites. From all locations, backgrounds and walks of life, who deserve more …&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Innovative work. Growth opportunities. Caring co-workers. And a chance to do work that fills us with a sense of purpose.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the idea of working on tech that helps people do good in the world lights you up ... If you want a career where you’re valued for who you are and challenged to see who you can become …&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s time to join Benevity. We’re so excited to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where We Work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Benevity, we embrace a flexible hybrid approach to where we work that empowers our people in a way that supports great work, strong relationships, and personal well-being. For those located near one of our offices, while there’s no set requirement for in-office time, we do value the moments when coming together in person helps us build connection and collaboration. Whether it’s for onboarding, project work, or a chance to align and bond as a team, we trust our people to make thoughtful decisions about when showing up in person matters most.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join a company where DEIB isn’t a buzzword&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Diversity, equity, inclusion and belonging are part of Benevity’s DNA. You’ll see the impact of our massive investment in DEIB daily — from our well-supported employee resources groups to the exceptional diversity on our leadership and tech teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We know that diverse backgrounds, experiences, skills and passions are what move our business and our people forward, so we&#39;re committed to creating a culture of belonging with equal opportunities for everyone to shine.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That starts with a fair and accessible hiring process. If you want to feel seen, heard and celebrated, you belong at Benevity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates with disabilities who may require accommodations throughout the hiring or assessment process are encouraged to reach out to accommodations@benevity.com.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Visier is the global leader in Workforce Intelligence that powers every people decision. We bring Workforce AI to life for HR departments through our award-winning, agentic AI technology by surfacing the insights leaders need to plan, decide, and act with confidence in the moments that matter most. As the market leader in people analytics, workforce planning, organizational design, and manager effectiveness solutions, we fuel smarter decision-making for organizations across the globe. Our mission is to help businesses lead with insight at scale as they continuously transform.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Founded in 2010 by the pioneers of business intelligence, we have over 85,000 customers in 75 countries—including enterprises like BASF, Panasonic, Domino’s Pizza, Experian, Amgen, eBay, and Ford Motor Company.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Procurement Contract Specialist will be the primary purchaser facilitating Visier’s third-party technology, services, partnership, and marketing ecosystem. You aren&#39;t just &quot;buying software&quot;—you are a central hub of Visier purchasing responsible for ensuring that every dollar Visier spends on technology is an investment in our scalability and security. You will partner with internal business leaders to navigate vendor landscapes, structure contracts, and manage the end-to-end procurement lifecycle. You will be the trusted expert who ensures our vendor partnerships are compliant, cost-effective, and aligned with our long-term roadmap.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing...&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the purchasing contact for internal business units for all purchase transactions, including SaaS and technology purchases, marketing and event rentals and leasing, and professional services engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Efficiently drive all stages of the procurement process, from initial vendor discovery, to diligence and review, to final contract negotiation and execution, to post-signature record keeping and documentation, removing friction while maintaining consistent standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead discussions with vendors on pricing, renewals, service level agreements (SLAs), and other commercial terms to ensure Visier receives maximum value and favorable risk profiles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a portfolio of concurrent renewals and new acquisitions, ensuring contracts adhere to our internal governance, data privacy, and security policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor for and suggest opportunities for optimization in our current and evolving tech stack, and work with internal stakeholders to ensure vendor selection is aligned to organizational goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion best practices by enabling internal stakeholders to effectively scope requirements and manage vendor performance post-signature.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring to the Table...&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of dedicated procurement experience, ideally within a SaaS or high-growth technology environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of negotiating and closing inbound technology deals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A high degree of autonomous operation, with a commitment to rigor, organization, and diligence necessary to ensure accurate and complete records and tracking of all company purchases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to review, understand, and make recommendations when it comes to contract language, risk acceptance, and acceptable compromises; you are the primary source for all contract reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative internal partnering, and a level of comfort navigating unfamiliar circumstances with poise and good judgment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with modern procurement solutions, such as Coupa, Service Now, and Jira, an interest in leveraging AI for optimized results, and a working knowledge of G-Drive and its suite of products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A High-Velocity Mindset—you operate with urgency and precision, understanding that the business moves fast and procurement should be an accelerator, not a bottleneck.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You possess a personality that exudes confidence and &quot;commercial &quot;savviness. Our internal teams should view you as their expert in getting things purchased.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🌱 Most importantly, you share our values…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You roll up your sleeves&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You make it easy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are proud&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You never stop learning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You play to win&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🚀 How we work &amp;amp; what we offer...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fixed hybrid work model: 3 days a week in office (Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modern, pet-friendly downtown office spaces with collaborative areas and an on-site gym&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual company All Hands in Vancouver, our entire organization travels to our Vancouver HQ for a week of team building, learning and breakout sessions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary, and top-tier health and wellness benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stock options and/or bonus based on your role, location, and employment type&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous paid time off, including volunteering days and extra days over the December holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The base pay range for this position in the &lt;strong&gt;$&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5&lt;/strong&gt;3,200 - 76,000 CAD &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;/ year + bonus&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Benefits and working arrangements may vary depending on your seniority, location and employment type. The compensation offered will be determined by factors such as relevant qualifications, experience, knowledge and skills. Many of our positions are eligible for additional types of compensation (e.g., commission plans, bonus, etc.) which our Talent Acquisition team will share with you if you interview for the role.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
