&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.visier.com/candidate-privacy-notice-and-recruiter-policy/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visier Candidate Privacy Notice and Recruiter Policy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Visier is the global leader in Workforce Intelligence that powers every people decision. We bring Workforce AI to life for HR departments through our award-winning, agentic AI technology by surfacing the insights leaders need to plan, decide, and act with confidence in the moments that matter most. As the market leader in people analytics, workforce planning, organizational design, and manager effectiveness solutions, we fuel smarter decision-making for organizations across the globe. Our mission is to help businesses lead with insight at scale as they continuously transform.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Founded in 2010 by the pioneers of business intelligence, we have over 85,000 customers in 75 countries—including enterprises like BASF, Panasonic, Domino’s Pizza, Experian, Amgen, eBay, and Ford Motor Company.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a Sr. BI Analyst at Visier, you are a high-level technical lead sitting at the intersection of internal operations and product innovation. You serve as a strategic consultant to our People &amp;amp; Culture (P&amp;amp;C) leadership, transforming complex workforce data into the narratives that drive our global business strategy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a compelling role. We aren’t just looking for someone to build internal dashboards; you are a &quot;product-minded&quot; analyst who understands how data translates into the insights Visier needs to make informed talent and business decisions. You’ll learn the industry-leading people analytics platform and then consult with the business to identify impactful use cases and insights. You’ll help define the &quot;why&quot; and the &quot;what’s next&quot; for both our leadership and the People and Culture team to make sure we’re always ‘drinking our champagne’.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is based out of our Yaletown office in downtown Vancouver.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will be doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Consultation &amp;amp; Advisory:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as a key consultant to the P&amp;amp;C team and senior leadership. You will take high-level, strategic objectives and required insights and independently define, design, and deliver the project and technical deliverables required to meet them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Independent Project Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Successfully manage projects and technical assignments of large and complex scope. You will work without supervision, leading the end-to-end evaluation of our data model and workforce trends while ensuring project outcomes align with objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product &amp;amp; AI Innovation:&lt;/strong&gt; Champion innovation by partnering with Product teams to drive technical changes. You will identify complex data signals and &quot;intangibles&quot; from our internal workforce and business data to influence new product features and validate the effectiveness of our workforce AI models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advanced Data Governance:&lt;/strong&gt; Demonstrate independent judgment in maintaining a &quot;single source of truth.&quot; You will resolve complex issues regarding data integrity across Workday, Peakon, and our proprietary Visier People Application&amp;nbsp; using creative and highly effective solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Insight Synthesis:&lt;/strong&gt; Translate high-level business challenges into sophisticated data narratives. You will apply an advanced level of analysis to turnover, sentiment, and headcount data to provide in-depth evaluations that impact overall organization success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optimizing Operational Delivery:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive operational efficiency by collaborating with the internal teams to track performance metrics and ensure the timely execution of all departmental deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High Influence&lt;/strong&gt;: Serve as a product champion by driving internal adoption of Visier People and ensuring platform insights are a foundational element of all departmental decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring to the table:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advanced Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 6+ years in a BI or Data Analytics role, with a record of resolving complex issues in creative ways within a SaaS or HR Tech environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Mastery &amp;amp; Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Advanced-level SQL and deep expertise in data visualization. You lead by example and may function as a lead for cross-functional work groups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Independent Judgment:&lt;/strong&gt; A proven ability to work without supervision, applying advanced analysis to resolve complex situations where multiple variable factors are at play.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Impact:&lt;/strong&gt; A track record of taking initiative to drive process or technical changes across a business. You are seen as a subject matter expert who can influence the thinking of stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Domain Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt; Advanced understanding of HR metrics and the HR tech stack (Workday, Greenhouse, etc.), coupled with an expert-level ability to evangelize the &quot;Visier Way&quot; of people analytics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Edge:&lt;/strong&gt; A strategic understanding of how Machine Learning models consume data and the foresight to drive the future of AI-driven workforce insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🌱 &lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Most importantly, you share our values…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You roll up your sleeves&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You make it easy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are proud&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You never stop learning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You play to win&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🚀 How we work &amp;amp; what we offer...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fixed hybrid work model: 3 days a week in office (Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modern, pet-friendly downtown office spaces with collaborative areas and an on-site gym&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual company All Hands in Vancouver, our entire organization travels to our Vancouver HQ for a week of team building, learning and breakout sessions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary, and top-tier health and wellness benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stock options and/or bonus based on your role, location, and employment type&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous paid time off, including volunteering days and extra days over the December holidays&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The base pay range for this position in the &lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;90,000-115,000 &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;/ year + bonus&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Benefits and working arrangements may vary depending on your seniority, location and employment type. The compensation offered will be determined by factors such as relevant qualifications, experience, knowledge and skills. Many of our positions are eligible for additional types of compensation (e.g., commission plans, bonus, etc.) which our Talent Acquisition team will share with you if you interview for the role.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #2bd9d9; font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;@visier_inc&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt; - &lt;/strong&gt;@visier_inc&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #2bd9d9; font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/company/visier-analytics/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Linkedin&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; - https://www.linkedin.com/company/visier-analytics/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.visier.com/candidate-privacy-notice-and-recruiter-policy/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visier Candidate Privacy Notice and Recruiter Policy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Visier is the global leader in Workforce Intelligence that powers every people decision. We bring Workforce AI to life for HR departments through our award-winning, agentic AI technology by surfacing the insights leaders need to plan, decide, and act with confidence in the moments that matter most. As the market leader in people analytics, workforce planning, organizational design, and manager effectiveness solutions, we fuel smarter decision-making for organizations across the globe. Our mission is to help businesses lead with insight at scale as they continuously transform.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Founded in 2010 by the pioneers of business intelligence, we have over 85,000 customers in 75 countries—including enterprises like BASF, Panasonic, Domino’s Pizza, Experian, Amgen, eBay, and Ford Motor Company.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a Test Developer Co-op at Visier, you will work with the Test Enablement Team and will be responsible for ensuring the integrity of the Visier application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our co-op experience is unique and designed to prepare you for professional success as you work on real, impactful work from the beginning...not features that may be mothballed after 8 months of hard work! Our ultimate goal is to give you the mentorship, training, and work experience you need to start your career. A number of our students return to us after they graduate and start developing their professional career at Visier! We use a variety of frontend technologies including Angular, NgRx, Play Framework, TypeScript, Less, and others. We deal with large volumes of data every day. And in our backend areas we work with technologies like Scala, Kafka, Consul, Cassandra DB, Docker, AWS, etc. So, you’ll be developing knowledge and skills that are transferable anywhere.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manual testing, building automated tests, and data validation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with developers to create and sign off on test plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Writing end-to-end UI automated tests and REST tests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Setting up Jenkins CI pipeline to automate common tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performing final checks to ensure the software we release is beautiful&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll bring to the table...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coding skills in writing functional tests using Selenium, Playwright, and REST Assured&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some knowledge in one of the following areas:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of data structures and algorithms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of web technologies (REST, XML, JSON, Angular14)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of SQL databases and SQL language is an asset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail, tendency to spot mistakes and identify potential improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Most importantly, you share our values...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You &lt;strong&gt;roll up your sleeves&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You &lt;strong&gt;make it easy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You &lt;strong&gt;are proud&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&lt;strong&gt; never stop learning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&lt;strong&gt; play to win&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
