&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Visier is the global leader in Workforce Intelligence that powers every people decision. We bring Workforce AI to life for HR departments through our award-winning, agentic AI technology by surfacing the insights leaders need to plan, decide, and act with confidence in the moments that matter most. As the market leader in people analytics, workforce planning, organizational design, and manager effectiveness solutions, we fuel smarter decision-making for organizations across the globe. Our mission is to help businesses lead with insight at scale as they continuously transform.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Founded in 2010 by the pioneers of business intelligence, we have over 85,000 customers in 75 countries—including enterprises like BASF, Panasonic, Domino’s Pizza, Experian, Amgen, eBay, and Ford Motor Company.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing...&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a high-performing IT team and provide great customer experience to internal stakeholders across the company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with business stakeholders to successfully manage and grow customer and prospect facing IT services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the Information Security and R&amp;amp;D teams to align and improve upon technology strategies and cybersecurity measures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Visier’s IT, including core infrastructure, cloud services and desktop support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively communicate IT recommendations and KPIs to the leadership team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a budget and lead negotiations with vendors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing and executing various projects, such as technology expenditures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct workload, perform resource allocation, measure results and writing regular status reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhance a knowledge base system for IT procedures and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with various stakeholders internally and build strong trusted relationships with business partners to ensure the team’s operational efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What you&#39;ll bring to the table...&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree in Information Systems, Computer Science, or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of progressive IT leadership experience, specifically within a&amp;nbsp;SaaS or high-tech environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience leading a high-performance technology team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with successfully managing internal and customer facing IT services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Project Manager, you have the ability to translate strategy into successful execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have previously owned IT strategy and budget and can demonstrate experience in developing and executing it in a software/high-tech company during a high-growth stage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to build strong relationships with multiple stakeholders to ensure alignment between IT and business objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A highly effective communicator, you are practiced in providing well-thought-out assessments and recommendations to the executive team, including best practices and emerging technology trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most importantly, you share our values...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You roll up your sleeves&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You make it easy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are proud&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You never stop learning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You play to win&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The base pay range for this position in the Canada is $140k - $220k / year + bonus&lt;/p&gt;
